{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"zotero":1,"inscriptions":5},{"title":2,"date":3,"citation":4},"Sicile","1896","\u003Cspan>Paolo Orsi, « Sicile », \u003Ci>Bulletin de Correspondance Hellénique\u003C/i> 20 (1896): 399‑400\u003C/span>",[6,99,146,211,258,305],{"file":7,"uri":7,"title":8,"status":9,"editionAuthor":11,"type":12,"objectType":16,"material":20,"condition":24,"layoutDesc":25,"handNote":32,"date":46,"places":51,"geo":60,"country":64,"region":65,"settlement":66,"repository":67,"idno":71,"textLang":74,"provenance":53,"letterHeights":78,"publications":79,"zotero":83,"keywords":87,"html":98},"ISic001869","Funerary inscription for Artemo",{"_":10},"edited",null,{"_":13,"ana":14,"ref":15},"funerary","#function.funerary","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html",{"_":17,"ana":18,"ref":19},"block","#object.block","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/189.html",{"_":21,"ana":22,"ref":23},"limestone","#material.stone.limestone","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html","",{"layout":26},{"p":27,"rs":28,"damage":24},"Three lines of Greek letters, seemingly not centered / regularly laid out.",{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"lettering":33,"dimensions":34},"Described by Orsi (1896) as 'scritto a pessimi caratteri', and (1899) as 'lettere cattive, rustiche cosi che a tutta prima sembrano archaiche, e molto sconservate... L'iscrizione negligentemente redatta e scolpita è funebre di tarda età'. Pace states 'lettere del III sec. av. Cr.', but given the presence of lunate epsilon and Orsi's comments, a later date seems much more likely.",[35,42],{"type":36,"l":37,"from":38,"to":39,"h":40,"unit":41},"letterHeight","Line 1-3","line1","line3","55-95","mm",{"type":43,"l":44,"from":38,"to":45,"unit":41},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","line2",{"_":47,"notBefore":48,"notAfter":49,"evidence":50},"Suggested to be of later Roman date by Orsi on the basis of lettering etc.",101,400,"lettering",[52,56],{"_":53,"type":54,"ref":55},"Kamarina","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462126",{"_":57,"type":58,"ref":59},"Santa Croce Camerina","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/6540853",[61],[62,63],36.8736,14.4507,"Italy","Sicily","Siracusa",{"_":68,"role":69,"ref":70},"Museo Archeologico Regionale Paolo Orsi","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/097",{"_":72,"type":73},"16474","inventory",{"_":75,"mainLang":76,"languages":77},"Ancient Greek","grc",[75],[],[80,81,82],"Orsi, 1896, Sicile","Orsi, 1899, Camarina (Campagna archeologica del 1896)","Pace, 1927, Camarina: topografia, storia, archeologia",[84,85,86],"FWX5CWBN","ICW2M9P2","ZJ6KUFMM",[88,89,90,13,17,21,91,92,93,94,95,96,97,76],"isic001869","funerary inscription for artemo",{"_":10},"kamarina","santa croce camerina","italy","sicily","siracusa","museo archeologico regionale paolo orsi","ancient greek","Text encoding: Jonathan Prag, edition source:",{"file":100,"uri":100,"title":101,"status":102,"editionAuthor":11,"type":103,"objectType":107,"material":111,"condition":24,"layoutDesc":115,"handNote":119,"date":125,"places":129,"geo":132,"country":64,"region":65,"settlement":66,"repository":134,"idno":135,"textLang":137,"provenance":53,"letterHeights":139,"publications":140,"zotero":141,"keywords":142,"html":98},"ISic001870","Inscribed fragment of a marble basin",{"_":10},{"_":104,"ana":105,"ref":106},"dedication","#function.dedication","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/88.html",{"_":108,"ana":109,"ref":110},"basin","#object.basin","https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/144.html",{"_":112,"ana":113,"ref":114},"marble","#material.stone.marble","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html",{"layout":116},{"p":117,"rs":118,"damage":24},"Single line of letters on the outward facing side of the rim.",{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},{"lettering":120,"dimensions":121},"Presented as clearly incised archaic letters",[122,124],{"type":36,"l":123,"from":38,"to":38,"unit":41},"Line 1",{"type":43,"l":44,"from":38,"to":45,"unit":41},{"_":126,"notBefore":127,"notAfter":128,"evidence":50},"Archaic, on the basis of the lettering.",-600,-501,[130,131],{"_":53,"type":54,"ref":55},{"_":57,"type":58,"ref":59},[133],[62,63],{"_":68,"role":69,"ref":70},{"_":136,"type":73},"16484",{"_":75,"mainLang":76,"languages":138},[75],[],[80,81,82],[84,85,86],[143,144,145,104,108,112,91,92,93,94,95,96,97,76],"isic001870","inscribed fragment of a marble basin",{"_":10},{"file":147,"uri":147,"title":148,"status":149,"editionAuthor":11,"type":150,"objectType":151,"material":155,"condition":24,"layoutDesc":156,"handNote":160,"date":178,"places":181,"geo":187,"country":64,"region":65,"settlement":66,"repository":191,"idno":192,"textLang":194,"facsimile":196,"provenance":183,"letterHeights":203,"publications":204,"zotero":205,"keywords":206,"html":98},"ISic001871","Funerary inscription for Gamike",{"_":10},{"_":13,"ana":14,"ref":15},{"_":152,"ana":153,"ref":154},"plaque","#object.plaque","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259",{"_":21,"ana":22,"ref":23},{"layout":157},{"p":158,"rs":159,"damage":24},"Text over five lines, carefully following guidelines to the base of each line, with a marginal guideline to the left and right, with the left margin consistently observed. An additional guideline below is unused; the guidelines carefully align with the text to the right of this one. Use of a vacat prior to the age at death.",{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},{"lettering":161,"dimensions":162},"Deep and wide slightly crude v-cut, producing consistent fairly square letters without serifs. Alpha has mostly downward left sloping cross-bar; epsilon is lunate with mostly shorter middle bar; zeta has slight curvature to the strokes; kappa has short arms; mu has four full-length diagonal strokes; lunate sigma, but note final square lunate for digamma / stigma for numeral 6.",[163,165,168,170,174,177],{"type":36,"l":123,"from":38,"to":38,"h":164,"unit":41},"27-30",{"type":36,"l":166,"from":45,"to":45,"h":167,"unit":41},"Line 2","25-30",{"type":36,"l":169,"from":39,"to":39,"h":167,"unit":41},"Line 3",{"type":36,"l":171,"from":172,"to":172,"h":173,"unit":41},"Line 4","line4","21-30",{"type":36,"l":175,"from":176,"to":176,"h":167,"unit":41},"Line 5","line5",{"type":43,"l":44,"from":38,"to":45,"unit":41},{"_":179,"notBefore":48,"notAfter":180,"evidence":50},"Roman imperial in date",300,[182,185],{"_":183,"type":54,"ref":184},"Syracusae","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462503",{"_":66,"type":58,"ref":186},"http://sws.geonames.org/2523083",[188],[189,190],37.08415,15.27628,{"_":68,"role":69,"ref":70},{"_":193,"type":73},"15083",{"_":75,"mainLang":76,"languages":195},[75],{"n":197,"url":198,"height":199,"width":200,"desc":201,"surfaceType":202},"screen","ISic001871_tiled.tif","3680px","5520px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Parco archeologico e paesaggistico di Siracusa, Eloro, Villa del Tellaro e Akrai, and the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-04-29.","front",[],[80],[84],[207,208,209,13,152,21,210,95,93,94,95,96,97,76],"isic001871","funerary inscription for gamike",{"_":10},"syracusae",{"file":212,"uri":212,"title":213,"status":214,"editionAuthor":11,"type":215,"objectType":216,"material":217,"condition":24,"layoutDesc":218,"handNote":222,"date":239,"places":240,"geo":243,"country":64,"region":65,"settlement":66,"repository":245,"idno":246,"textLang":247,"facsimile":249,"provenance":183,"letterHeights":251,"publications":252,"zotero":253,"keywords":254,"html":98},"ISic001872","Funerary inscription for Mousa",{"_":10},{"_":13,"ana":14,"ref":15},{"_":152,"ana":153,"ref":154},{"_":21,"ana":22,"ref":23},{"layout":219},{"p":220,"rs":221,"damage":24},"Text over six lines, set in a recessed panel in the style of a temple facade, but without guidelines. Some use of interpuncts and vacats in the text.",{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},{"lettering":223,"dimensions":224},"Text is deeply incised in letters of slightly varying size. Extensive use of serifs, with several letters tending to the cursive. Alpha has straight bar, curving ends; epsilon is lunate with equal length mid-bar; zeta is large and curved; kappa has near full-length arms; mu has slanting strokes that reach the lower line, but often join before the top and have extended upper strokes; pi has overlapping cross bar; rho has closed eye; sigma is lunate. Elegant hedera in line 2; use of vacats in age at death.",[225,227,229,231,232,234,238],{"type":36,"l":123,"from":38,"to":38,"h":226,"unit":41},"25-31",{"type":36,"l":166,"from":45,"to":45,"h":228,"unit":41},"20-22",{"type":36,"l":169,"from":39,"to":39,"h":230,"unit":41},"19-25",{"type":36,"l":171,"from":172,"to":172,"h":230,"unit":41},{"type":36,"l":175,"from":176,"to":176,"h":233,"unit":41},"19-21",{"type":36,"l":235,"from":236,"to":236,"h":237,"unit":41},"Line 6","line6","20-21",{"type":43,"l":44,"from":38,"to":45,"unit":41},{"_":179,"notBefore":48,"notAfter":180,"evidence":50},[241,242],{"_":183,"type":54,"ref":184},{"_":66,"type":58,"ref":186},[244],[189,190],{"_":68,"role":69,"ref":70},{"_":193,"type":73},{"_":75,"mainLang":76,"languages":248},[75],{"n":197,"url":250,"height":199,"width":200,"desc":201,"surfaceType":202},"ISic001872_tiled.tif",[],[80],[84],[255,256,257,13,152,21,210,95,93,94,95,96,97,76],"isic001872","funerary inscription for mousa",{"_":10},{"file":259,"uri":259,"title":260,"status":261,"editionAuthor":11,"type":262,"objectType":263,"material":264,"condition":24,"layoutDesc":265,"handNote":273,"date":286,"places":287,"geo":290,"country":64,"region":65,"settlement":66,"repository":292,"idno":293,"textLang":294,"facsimile":296,"provenance":183,"letterHeights":298,"publications":299,"zotero":300,"keywords":301,"html":98},"ISic001873","Funerary inscription for Kopria",{"_":10},{"_":13,"ana":14,"ref":15},{"_":152,"ana":153,"ref":154},{"_":21,"ana":22,"ref":23},{"layout":266},{"p":267,"rs":268,"damage":24},"Text over five lines, neatly respecting gridlines to the base of each line and with marginal lines to left and right - that on the left is approximately followed, that on the right is ignored; an additional gridline below is unused. Some use of interpuncts and vacats in the text. The first line shows clear traces of red paint in the letters.",[269,270],{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},{"_":271,"ana":272},"rubrication, red colour","#execution.rubrication.red",{"lettering":274,"dimensions":275},"Text is incised in fairly tall, thin, neat and plain letters mostly without serifs. Alpha has downward left sloping cross-bar; epsilon is lunate, with shorter and sometimes detached middle bar; zeta is straight; eta sometimes has detached cross-bar (line 4); kapa has short arms; mu has angled strokes, the mid-strokes only descending half-way, and no upward extension of the apexes; omicron is slightly smaller than other letters; pi does not overlap; rho i slcosed; sigma is lunate. Use of a simple/stylised hedera in lines 2 and 4, and letters are somewhat irregularly spaced especially in the final line.",[276,278,280,281,283,285],{"type":36,"l":123,"from":38,"to":38,"h":277,"unit":41},"29-30 (omicron = 20)",{"type":36,"l":166,"from":45,"to":45,"h":279,"unit":41},"26-32",{"type":36,"l":169,"from":39,"to":39,"h":167,"unit":41},{"type":36,"l":171,"from":172,"to":172,"h":282,"unit":41},"24-30",{"type":36,"l":175,"from":176,"to":176,"h":284,"unit":41},"22-32",{"type":43,"l":44,"from":38,"to":45,"unit":41},{"_":179,"notBefore":48,"notAfter":180,"evidence":50},[288,289],{"_":183,"type":54,"ref":184},{"_":66,"type":58,"ref":186},[291],[189,190],{"_":68,"role":69,"ref":70},{"_":193,"type":73},{"_":75,"mainLang":76,"languages":295},[75],{"n":197,"url":297,"height":199,"width":200,"desc":201,"surfaceType":202},"ISic001873_tiled.tif",[],[80],[84],[302,303,304,13,152,21,210,95,93,94,95,96,97,76],"isic001873","funerary inscription for kopria",{"_":10},{"file":306,"uri":306,"title":307,"status":308,"editionAuthor":11,"type":309,"objectType":313,"material":317,"condition":24,"layoutDesc":318,"handNote":322,"date":423,"places":428,"geo":431,"country":64,"region":65,"settlement":66,"repository":433,"idno":434,"textLang":436,"facsimile":438,"provenance":183,"letterHeights":441,"publications":442,"zotero":450,"keywords":458,"html":98},"ISic003331","The Syracusans honour King Gelon, son of Hieron II",{"_":10},{"_":310,"ana":311,"ref":312},"honorific","#function.honorific","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/69.html",{"_":314,"ana":315,"ref":316},"base","#object.base","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/57.html",{"_":21,"ana":22,"ref":23},{"layout":319},{"p":320,"rs":321,"damage":24},"Three lines of finely carved Greek letters, centred on the stone (line one with short vacats at beginning and end, line 2 fully filling the face of the stone, line 3 centred with substantial vacats before and after.",{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},{"lettering":323,"dimensions":412},[324,325],"Elegant wide and very regular letters with thinly carved strokes. Broken bar alpha; beta with equal sized loops; epsilon with short middle bar; kappa with short arms; mu with vertical first and last, middle strokes to half-height; omicron normally full size but small in line 2 (compression a factor); rho with almost fully rounded eye; sigma with approximately horizontal top and bottom strokes or very slightly open; omega full-size rounded and open with straight feet.",{"_":326,"ref":327},"\n                                    Types list:\n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                ",[328,331,334,337,340,343,346,349,352,355,358,361,364,367,370,373,376,379,382,385,388,391,394,397,400,403,406,409],{"_":329,"target":330},"Α type2","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type2.html",{"_":332,"target":333},"Β type2","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Β-type2.html",{"_":335,"target":336},"Β type2.1","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Β-type2.1.html",{"_":338,"target":339},"Γ type2","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Γ-type2.html",{"_":341,"target":342},"Γ type2.2","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Γ-type2.2.html",{"_":344,"target":345},"Δ type2","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Δ-type2.html",{"_":347,"target":348},"Ε type2","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.html",{"_":350,"target":351},"Ε type2.3","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.html",{"_":353,"target":354},"Ε type2.3.1","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.1.html",{"_":356,"targ